President Trump welcomed Pastor Andrew Brunson and his family to the Oval Office after his release from a Turkish prison. The president thanked those who worked to secure Brunson's release and praised the pastor's strength and faith. Trump also expressed hope for a better relationship with Turkey and commented on the ongoing investigation into the disappearance of journalist Jamal Khashoggi. He stated that he would be speaking with Saudi Arabia's King Salman and making a determination on possible repercussions based on the facts of the case. The president also mentioned the possibility of sanctions on Turkey and discussed the future of U.S. arms sales to the country.